    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.14.13"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Neihardt Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">13</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        55 West 88,
                        New York,
                        March 26th,1929.
                    </dateline>
                
                    <salute>Friend Neihardt,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Not because you said some pleasant words about my book do I indict these lines but because <hi rend="caps">YOU SO WELL UNDERSTAND</hi>. Up to the present moment not a single soul of the heterogenious jury has had the prescience to know.Thank you for being an exception.</p>
                
                <p>It is particularly sweet that this comes to me from St.Louis, the city that saw me in the year 1883 when I,a mere youth,wrote special articles for <hi rend="caps">DIE WESTLICHE POST</hi>, as the proteg&#233; of Dr.Emil Pretorius.As such youth I organized the Ethical Culture Society of the original organizers of which Charles Nagel and Ben Altman,I believe, still survive.In 1916,when Hughes ran for the presidency of the United States, Missouri was my chief stamping ground for the Republican National Committee,but included in this itinerary was Indiana and part of Michigan;and as this was before I resumed the above family name,I was known by the first half:Dr. Adolphe Danziger.</p>
                
                <p>Hoping this will find you in good health and in the height of spirits, and wishing you the compliments of the season, I beg to remain</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Faithfully yours,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Adolphe de Castro</signed>
                    <note type="curatorial">Adolphe de Castro</note>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi>Neihardt Esq.,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>c/o Post-Dispatch,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>St.Louis, Mo.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <note>AdeC/LG.</note> 
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
